        "subject": "LU-3176 kernel: md/raid6 fix read-error correction",
        "message": "LU-3176 kernel: md/raid6 fix read-error correction\n\nmd/raid6 is not doing correct read-error when single disk failed\nand going to be degraded mode for one more drive.\nThe original code only considered raid5, but didn't work for raid6.\nThis is fixed in mainstream linux kernel.\nupstream commit 87aa63000c484bfb9909989316f615240dfee018\n\nSigned-off-by: Shuichi Ihara <sihara@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Iea654904512860d9ddd7de58fae8c88c401b4b1c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
